23/09/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Police arrested 60 people on Wednesday (September 22nd), including 22 police officers, for suspected smuggling. 
The large-scale operation was carried out in 60 locations, mostly in the south, and involved more than 200 policemen from both entities. 
The detainees are suspected of involvement in cigarette and luxury goods smuggling. 
(RTRS, AP, Reuters - 22/09/10)
